00:03:15.170 --> 00:03:20.270 align:middle line:84%
and that there actually
is a whole set of paths

00:03:20.270 --> 00:03:21.570 align:middle line:90%
for the householder.

00:03:21.570 --> 00:03:22.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Sure.

00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:25.880 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a little bit
about how the ascetic path

00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:28.340 align:middle line:84%
manifested or what are some
of the components of it

00:03:28.340 --> 00:03:32.150 align:middle line:84%
in traditional yoga
traditions versus some

00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:35.990 align:middle line:84%
of the different qualities
or different techniques

00:03:35.990 --> 00:03:37.460 align:middle line:90%
of the householder path?

00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:42.380 align:middle line:84%
>> The ascetic path, the monk's
path, is based on letting go.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:46.160 align:middle line:90%
It's actually based on loss.

00:03:46.160 --> 00:03:48.170 align:middle line:90%
You move to the ashram.

00:03:48.170 --> 00:03:49.790 align:middle line:90%
You get away from society.

00:03:49.790 --> 00:03:51.710 align:middle line:90%
You lose connection to society.

00:03:51.710 --> 00:03:54.620 align:middle line:90%
You lose connection to wealth.

00:03:54.620 --> 00:03:55.960 align:middle line:90%
You lose distractions.

00:03:55.960 --> 00:03:57.080 align:middle line:90%
>> And you give up family.

00:03:57.080 --> 00:03:58.190 align:middle line:90%
>> And you give up family.

00:03:58.190 --> 00:04:00.260 align:middle line:90%
You give up relationships.

00:04:00.260 --> 00:04:04.730 align:middle line:84%
And the focus is continually
on letting go, loss, letting

00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:07.370 align:middle line:84%
go, loss, less,
less, less, less,

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:10.100 align:middle line:84%
until there's nothing
left, until you finally

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:13.070 align:middle line:90%
connect to your true self.

00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:17.779 align:middle line:84%
The householder path is
based on fulfillment.

00:04:17.779 --> 00:04:21.410 align:middle line:84%
It's almost the opposite
where we're cultivating

00:04:21.410 --> 00:04:22.760 align:middle line:90%
the qualities of the heart.

00:04:22.760 --> 00:04:24.980 align:middle line:84%
We're cultivating
that inner bliss.

00:04:24.980 --> 00:04:28.100 align:middle line:84%
We're cultivating
fulfillment to the point

00:04:28.100 --> 00:04:30.540 align:middle line:90%
where we're unaffected.

00:04:30.540 --> 00:04:32.600 align:middle line:90%
We're not attached.

00:04:32.600 --> 00:04:35.480 align:middle line:84%
There's this analogy that I
love to use with my students

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:39.620 align:middle line:84%
that it's like walking
down the streets

00:04:39.620 --> 00:04:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and having your
wallet pickpocketed.

00:04:43.370 --> 00:04:48.890 align:middle line:84%
If you're a billionaire,
it's like you've

00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:53.300 align:middle line:84%
got so much in the bank, you've
got so much fullness within,

00:04:53.300 --> 00:04:57.830 align:middle line:84%
you have so many resources
that it doesn't affect you.

00:04:57.830 --> 00:05:03.200 align:middle line:84%
If you're poor and your wallet
has your last money and that's

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:08.210 align:middle line:84%
your last meal, it's
incredibly stressful.

00:05:08.210 --> 00:05:11.240 align:middle line:84%
And so, again, the
state of peace,

00:05:11.240 --> 00:05:14.900 align:middle line:84%
the state of non-attachment
for the householder

00:05:14.900 --> 00:05:18.630 align:middle line:90%
comes from fulfillment.

00:05:18.630 --> 00:05:24.480 align:middle line:84%
>> How does fulfillment relate
to something like gratitude?

00:05:24.480 --> 00:05:27.360 align:middle line:84%
Or instead of letting
go and releasing

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:30.900 align:middle line:84%
and having to let go and
free and rid ourselves

00:05:30.900 --> 00:05:32.400 align:middle line:84%
of all of these
things as if they're

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:34.320 align:middle line:84%
these shameful
tarnishes that we must

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:36.000 align:middle line:84%
get rid of because
they're our humanity

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:38.416 align:middle line:84%
and they're just terrible, and
if we get rid of them, then

00:05:38.416 --> 00:05:41.130 align:middle line:84%
we may ascend, but,
rather, what I'm

00:05:41.130 --> 00:05:44.640 align:middle line:84%
hearing you say is it's
more of a cultivation

00:05:44.640 --> 00:05:48.060 align:middle line:84%
of different aspects
of our awareness

00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:50.430 align:middle line:84%
or different aspects
